Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Program Manager Saskatoon , SK Description Position: Program ManagerOut of scopeDate: May 22, 2024FTE: 1.0 FTEStatus: PermanentLocation: Saskatoon, SKAccountability: This position is accountable to the Library DirectorOvertime Status: This position is a management position and thus exempt from provincial overtime legislative requirements.The Program Manager oversees programming for all 45 Wheatland Regional Library branches ensuring a high level of programming across the region. This position is a senior management position answering to and working closely with the Library Director/CEO or designate Travel within the region is required. Evening and weekend work is expected.Duties and Responsibilities:Under the direction of the Library Director/CEO Lead the development and execution of strategies and plans for region-wide programming based on the region’s strategic plan. Evaluate regional goals and adjust programming strategies to meet the goals. Compile statistics and indicators on programming initiatives. Coordinate library programs and events including Saskatchewan Library Week, Canadian Children’s Book Week, Summer Reading Club, Saskatchewan Indigenous Storytelling Month, and author tours. Coordinate multi-branch programming and community services events and activities. Interact/build relationships with community-based organizations such as literacy groups, community groups, and other service groups. Commitment to deliver consistent programming services to a diverse population. STEAM/STEM programming for children and teens including creation of circulating kits. Develop and recommend to the Library Director an annual budget for programming services. Provide leadership to, communicate with, and support the branches in all aspects of programming. Provides and coordinates ongoing branch training in all aspects of programming. Provide back up to the Branch Manager when required.Qualifications, knowledge, and skills: Post graduate university degree in library or information science from an accredited institution or a post-secondary degree with equivalent experience. Previous programming experience including planning, developing and delivering programs. Ability to program for patrons of all ages. Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to lead a diverse group of people. Demonstrated ability to work constructively in a collaborative decision-making process Strong project management and strategic thinking abilities. Ability to demonstrate creativity, innovation, and research skills. Demonstrate experience delivering goals that support the strategic priorities of an organization. Excellent oral and written communication skills, including tact and diplomacy. Ability to sustain cooperative, productive relationships with staff and patrons. A valid driver’s license and the ability to drive throughout the region as required. Criminal Record Check satisfactory to the employer will be required.Remuneration:Salary: $52,555-$60,640Includes a comprehensive benefit package, including health, dental and vison, life insurance, long term disability, defined pension plan (MEPP) and professional development opportunitiesInterested applicants are requested to submit a current resume and cover letter to the Administrative Manager (admin@wheatland.sk.ca) by June 19th, 2024.Only applicants who are selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation 52,555-60,640 Closes: 19 June, 2024 Wheatland Regional Library Saskatoon , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
