Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Children and Youth Services Librarian Hanover , ON Description Do you love kids, books, reading, educating and entertaining? Are you passionate about helping young people to learn and discover? Do you love to put together and lead activities for children from babies to young teens?Can you work with parents, teachers, caregivers and library staff?Are you energetic, flexible, creative, enthusiastic and hard working? If you enjoy getting to know local families in a friendly town, consider joining our team at Hanover Public Library! We need an outstanding Children’s and Youth Services Librarian to take our services to the next level. Your job will embrace everything we do for the littlest ones in our community. Your duties will include developing, promoting, conducting and evaluating programming for babies to young teens. You will manage and develop collections, provide guidance for young readers, and organize events and outreach. A full job description may be found on our website. Contact ccaskanette@hanover.ca with any questions. Hanover is a busy and growing town in a rural area central to Grey and Bruce counties. It has four schools and several daycares, including many private in home daycares that bring their attendants to storytime. Our library is a single site, located downtown on main street and serving the town and area. The library is open six days a week, and we have a team of twelve people, mostly part-time. Qualifications: Early Childhood Education qualification, and/or Library and Information Technician diploma, or related discipline. Minimum 2 years of experience working with children in an education or library setting. Experience assessing materials and developing book and resource collections for children &amp; teens. Experience building relationships and providing outreach to community partners.Experience cataloguing children's materials is considered an asset. A clear Police Vulnerable Sector Check will be required of the successful candidate, at their own expense. Skills: Excellent rapport with children and teens, as well as adults. Demonstrated knowledge of legislation affecting children’s services and public libraries. Highly self-motivated with the ability to perform job related duties with little to no supervision, and manage multiple tasks effectively. Considerable knowledge of the development, needs and abilities of children and teens. Ability to plan, develop, implement and maintain short and long term programmes and goals for children and youth services. Ability to deal effectively and courteously with the general public, all staff, other government/agencies/libraries and community groups. Proficiency in the use of Microsoft Office and Windows, as well as office equipment, various computer software programs, internet, and Integrated Library Systems (ILS). Excellent creative, organizational, communications, planning, public relations, interpersonal skills as well as the ability to work on a team. Ability to prepare and deliver Children and Youth Services activities, create attractive posters, displays etc. Hours of Work: average 29 hours per week. Working hours may include some evenings, Saturdays and Sundays. Wage: Hourly. $27.12 Starting date: Immediate. How to Apply: Indicate your interest and submit your application as soon as possible. Closing date is Saturday June 1 at 5 pm. Send your resume and cover letter, indicating where you saw this job posting, to:Carolyn Caskanette (CEO / Chief Librarian) ccaskanette@hanover.ca The Hanover Public Library is an Equal Opportunity Employer. In accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, 2005 and the Ontario Human Rights Code, the library will provide accommodations throughout the recruitment, selection and/or assessment process to applicants with disabilities. Applicants selected for interview need to inform the library of the nature of any accommodation(s) that you may require to ensure your equal participation. All personal information is collected under the authority of the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act and will be used for candidate selection. We thank each applicant for their interest. However, only candidates selected for interview will be contacted. Compensation 27.12 per hour Closes: 1 June, 2024 Hanover Public Library Hanover , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
