and confers with other department heads, the Director of Library Services, and the Chief Executive Officer to coordinate work and exchange information. Maintains the Library e-Resource collection by selecting, promoting, collecting statistics, as well as training and assisting library employees with the resources.Acts as back-up for basic cataloguing and processing duties during periods of vacation or illnessWorks with the Public Services Supervisor and Circulation Supervisor to ensure that staffing levels are adequately maintained for all departments and considers for approval all requests for time off in accordance with the provisions of the collective agreement. Provides training and support to all library staff in the use of the Library’s ILS, in collaboration with other department heads. Oversees the work of the department including the development of procedures and the monitoring of performance of cataloguing and technical services. Confers with external ILS system support staff to troubleshoot and/or enhance the utilization of the ILS.Maintains an awareness of emerging trends in the delivery of public library services.Maintains standards of professional performance by example and direction.On emergency calling list with the alarm monitoring company. Acts as Person in Charge of the Library as required.Performs related duties as assigned. WORKING CONDITIONS: Usual office environment. Limited contact with the public. Moderate physical effort required, including handling of materials of moderate weight, pushing and pulling of carts, etc. Frequent use of equipment such as keyboards, requiring speed and accuracy. SALARY RATE AND RANGE: $50.59/hr to $57.69/hr (2023 rates) APPLICATION DEADLINE:4:00 pm on June 7, 2024 This is a bargaining unit position, CUPE Local 1146-Library Unit. Library Unit employees will first be given consideration for this vacancy followed by other applicants. Interested persons are requested to submit a cover letter and resume to: Lori Peixoto Administrative Assistant Woodstock Public Library 445 Hunter Street Woodstock ON N4S 4G7 lpeixoto@mywpl.ca Only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Personal information is collected in accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Personal Privacy Act. The Woodstock Public Library Board is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. Accommodations are available for all parts of the recruitment process. Applicants need to make their needs known in advance. Compensation 50.59/hr to 57.69/hr Closes: 7 June, 2024 Woodstock Public Library Woodstock , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
