Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Information Services &amp; Marketing Librarian I: Full-time (Permanent) Woodstock , ON Description WOODSTOCK PUBLIC LIBRARY INTERNAL/EXTERNAL JOB POSTING 2024-06 Information Services &amp; Marketing Librarian I: Full-time (Permanent) DATE: May 23, 2024 JOB TITLE: Information Services &amp; Marketing Librarian CLASSIFICATION: Reference Librarian I HOURS OF WORK: Thirty-five (35) hours per week. Schedule is subject to change and is not negotiable. May include evenings and weekends. NATURE OF POSITION: Reporting to the Public Services Supervisor, the Information Services &amp; Marketing Librarian splits their time between performing public service duties on the information desks, and creating, scheduling, and responding to the library’s print and social media promotions. This position may also attend library events for marketing and promotional purposes. QUALIFICATIONS: A Master’s Degree in Library Science from an ALA accredited library school.Demonstrated ability to personally produce high-quality, visually appealing, accessible marketing materials, both online and print. Graphic design experience an asset.Demonstrated knowledge of and experience with social media and social media scheduling technology, newsletters (print and electronic), and digital design programs.Knowledge of print and electronic information services and resources.Accuracy and attention to detail.Proven critical thinking skills.Excellent interpersonal, customer service, and communication skills. DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILTIES: Answers requests from the public for information and reference utilizing the resources of the Woodstock Public Library.Demonstrates customer service excellence in the delivery of reader’s advisory and information requests from the public.Selects, requests, and utilizes resources available through interlibrary loan to answer requests from the public and reference as appropriate.Operates equipment including photocopiers, microfilm readers and printers, personal computers, and peripheral devices.Performs some circulation functions including placing holds, updating PINs and account status.Instructs the public in the use of library resources, facilities, and equipment. Creates and schedules promotional materials (print and electronic) for social media, e-Newsletter, and print formats in consultation with programming and supervisory staff. Represents the voice of the library when responding to social media and email inquiries during scheduled hours, and refers as necessary.Refers media requests to appropriate senior staff.Collaborates with Senior Team on the development of promotional and branding strategies and publishing standards.Collaborates with Outreach staff to promote public engagement.Assumes the duties of the Person in Charge as scheduled.Other related duties as assigned. SALARY RATE AND RANGE:$37.10/hr to $40.57/hr (2023 rates) APPLICATION DEADLINE:4:00 pm, June 7, 2024 This is a bargaining unit position, CUPE Local 1146-Library Unit. Library Unit employees will first be given consideration for this vacancy followed by other applicants. Interested persons are requested to submit a cover letter and resume to: Lori Peixoto Administrative Assistant Woodstock Public Library 445 Hunter Street Woodstock ON N4S 4G7 lpeixoto@mywpl.ca Personal information is collected in accordance with the Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Personal Privacy Act. The Woodstock Public Library Board is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. Accommodations are available for all parts of the recruitment process. Applicants need to make their needs known in advance. Compensation 37.10/hr to 40.57/hr Closes: 7 June, 2024 Woodstock Public Library Woodstock , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
