Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Manager: Information Services Lethbridge , AB Description The Lethbridge Public Library proudly acknowledges that we are located at the heart of Siksikaitsitapi (Blackfoot) Territory, home of Kainai, Piikani, Siksika and Amskapi Piikani (Montana, USA) First Nations. Lethbridge is also located within the Métis Nation of Alberta, Region III. What we are looking for: Lethbridge Public Library is a welcoming, inclusive space. We connect and strengthen community through equitable access to learning and leisure. We are looking for candidates who will embrace and live our mission statement every day. Do you thrive on developing community connections? Do you have a deep commitment to public library values? Are you skilled at developing staff and committed to building services to meet community needs? We are seeking a leader to take on the continued development of the Information Services department. Responsibilities include service development, implementation, and evaluation as identified in the Plan of Service; developing and maintaining relationships with related organizations; monitoring budgets and general oversight; leading the staff IDEA (Inclusion, Equity, Diversity and Accessibility) Circle; and direct supervision of staff. We invite applications from candidates who may not have followed a traditional educational or professional path. We are interested in identifying and interviewing candidates who have experience with underserved or marginalized communities and who are committed to advancing our mission to provide equitable access to information resources. Your average day at LPL includes: Managing the operations of Information Services, including Indigenous Services. Developing, coordinating, and evaluating library services for adults, seniors, and Indigenous populations. Developing, promoting and maintaining relationships with relevant community organizations. Coordinating the implementation of community driven adult collections, programs and reference services and procedure changes Library-wide. Engaging in partnering and outreach efforts with community partners to expand library services to the wider community. Identifying and working to reduce gaps and barriers that limit progress in DEI in all aspects of library service, including collections, programming, and outreach. Leading staff teams and ensuring appropriate staff training and development to support the growth and development of the team. Working with other managers to develop and maintain a Library training program that ensures exemplary customer service. Liaising with appropriate Library staff and managers to ensure a lens of diversity, equity and inclusion is being applied to all public services. Assisting in developing and monitoring budgets related to their areas of responsibility. Working with other Managers to develop strategies for library collections, programming, outreach and services that meet the needs of the community. Working with other Managers to develop and implement strategies and plans to meet the Plan of Service priorities. Working with the Library Management Team to ensure a safe and healthy workplace for staff and customers. Actively participating in the development of Library policies, generally as they relate to information services. Resolving customer concerns and inquiries with a focus on positive customer relations. Communicating and collaborating with Chinook Arch Regional Library System staff, regional member libraries, and the Alberta library community. Representing the Library on committees, internal and external, and actively participating in the greater professional community. Performing administrative on call duties as required. What you need to bring to this position:MLIS, Masters in Library and Information Science degree from an ALA accredited institution.Candidates without an MLIS, with a strong background in libraries with some management experience will also be considered.Three or more years of supervisory experience, preferably at the branch or department head level or equivalent.Demonstrated commitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion including a strong record of engagement with partners in equity, diversity, and inclusion at the institutional level.Competency in working with historically marginalized groups.Experience with collection development, programming, and service evaluation and development, with a focus on public library services for adults, seniors or Indigenous populations is an asset.Proven ability to supervise staff, assess training and development needs, and evaluate and improve staff performance.Excellent organizational skills, including the ability to manage multiple, often competing priorities under pressure to meet tight deadlines.Ability to work independently and demonstrate initiative and problem solving.Ability to communicate effectively and maintain a good working relationship with internal and external groups.Demonstrated commitment to learn and develop professionally.Experience or interest in community driven service development.to apply: https://tre.tbe.taleo.net/tre01/ats/myView/Dashboard.jsp?tabs=Y Compensation $90,031.50 to $108,049.50 Closes: 1 June, 2024 Lethbridge Public Library Lethbridge , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
