Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Services Officer Toronto , ON Description Do you want to work for an organization where people care about each other?We are currently looking for a highly motivated, enthusiastic and experienced Library Services Officer.In this challenging position, you will report to the Library Services Manager and be responsible for providing technical services, resource organization, instructional support, and day-to-day access in-person and online to faculty, staff, and students, in support of learning, teaching, scholarship, and research in naturopathy. This includes being the primary point of contact for in-person and online services, developing teaching and learning guides for faculty and students, delivering information literacy workshops, checking-in and shelving materials, performing original and copy cataloguing, and processing document delivery requests. In consultation with colleagues you work to ensure the College’s ends as they relate to learning and teaching are met. QUALIFICATIONS: Library Technician diploma required (completion of RDA, MARC Coding &amp; Derived Cataloguing course or equivalent)Minimum one (1) year work experience in a Health Sciences library or similar environmentBackground in teaching and learning principles, evidenced by formal education, or demonstrated interest in higher education, pedagogy, or related fields an asset.Additional post-secondary education is an assetExceptional communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to deal effectively– both orally and in writing- with individuals at all levels within the organizationDemonstrable computer skills including Microsoft Office Suite, bibliographic databases, web-based applications and related software programs (e.g. Insignia Library System, Moodle LMS)Excellent organization and time management skillsTact, discretion and ability to exercise professional judgment in a highly confidential environment The Canadian College of Naturopathic Medicine (CCNM), is Canada’s premier, pan-Canadian academic institution for education and research in naturopathic medicine. Our graduates are eligible to write the licensing examinations for all regulated jurisdictions in Canada and the United States to become naturopathic doctors. The College is a registered charity dependent upon tuition, research grants and donations for the fulfillment of its mission. CCNM has two campuses, one in Toronto and another in the Metro Vancouver area known as the Boucher Campus. The College provides an attractive work environment for those who value good health and who enjoy working in a positive creative atmosphere. To Apply: Submit your resume and cover letter through the link here: Library Services Officer CCNM welcomes individuals who have demonstrated commitment to upholding the values of equity, diversity, and inclusion and will partner with us in expanding our EDI capacity. We encourage applications from equity-deserving groups, including Indigenous Peoples, Black-identified persons, other racialized persons, persons with disabilities and those who identify as women and/or LGBTQ2SIA+. CCNM is committed to accommodating applicants with disabilities throughout the recruitment process in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). Please advise the Human Resources department if you require accommodation at any stage of the recruitment process. This document can be made available in an alternate format upon request. On the covering letter, please indicate the title of the position that you are applying for, and where you saw this job advertisement. We thank all applicants in advance and advise that only those who are selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $50,000.00 - $51,000.00 Closes: 31 May, 2024 Canadian College of Naturopathic Medicine Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
